"content": "<h2>Lilies admired for their beauty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:22-Luke12:31\">LUK 12:22–12:31</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:34\">MAT 6:25–6:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:16\">SNG 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:5\">SNG 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song6:2-Song6:3\">SNG 6:2–6:3</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of lilies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:1-Song2:2\">SNG 2:1–2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:13\">SNG 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:2\">SNG 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:5\">HOS 14:5</a></p>\n<h2>Ornamental representations of lilies adorned Solomon's temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:19\">1KI 7:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:22\">1KI 7:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:25-1Kgs7:26\">1KI 7:25–7:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr4:4-2Chr4:5\">2CH 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h2>Lilies mentioned in some titles of tunes in the Psalms</h2>\n<p><strong>PSA 69:0</strong> <em>See also</em> PSA 45:0, PSA 60:0, PSA 80:0</p>",
